Utilities are revenue neutral meaning they cannot make any profit from the purchase and sale of natural gas on behalf of their customers as regulated by public utility commissions. Utilities that have experienced deregulation allow transport because third party suppliers do not alter their revenue stream.
Variable Rate
If you desire to go with the market, our Variable Rate Program provides you with the flexibility to ride current market prices with the opportunity to lock in rates at any time.

Guaranteed Savings

Guaranteed Fixed Price
Our Guaranteed Fixed Price takes the headache out of managing your budget and locks what you’re paying per unit at one set price for up to 60 months.
- Protects you against market volatility from weather-driven demand or other causes
- The program can be customized with full or partial loads based on the operations of your business

Price Protection
Protect yourself from extreme price fluctuations with our Price Protection Program. This program follows the market but sets a maximum cap price per therm.
- The price will fluctuate with the market but is guaranteed to not go over the capped price
- Protects your budget from large increases in price, while giving you to option to maximize value when prices decrease

content.content: Frequently Asked Questions
What is gas transport?

In deregulated markets, gas can be delivered onto the utility system and to commercial customers by third party suppliers such as WoodRiver Energy through a program known as gas transportation. Deregulation and gas transportation have been around since the early 1990’s but only recently has it been viable for smaller commercial customers to participate.
Benefits of gas transport

Transport allows customers to choose how they purchase their natural gas. Because we work with predictable loads we can efficiently deliver natural gas which in turn allows us to offer you the best rates and services possible. Our products are designed to service specific customer needs including budget certainty or savings. Ultimately, we want to help you find the right solution that best fits your needs.
Why do utilities allow transport?

Utilities are revenue neutral meaning they cannot make any profit from the purchase and sale of natural gas on behalf of their customers as regulated by public utility commissions. Utilities that have experienced deregulation allow transport because third party suppliers do not alter their revenue stream.
Does WoodRiver replace the utility?
WoodRiver does not replace the utility. Your local utility will still be the ones to call if you smell gas or if you suspect there is a leak.
Why choose WoodRiver?

WoodRiver Energy is passionate about our customers. We strive to provide all customers with the best service possible. As a small business ourselves we know what community means and we know how far a personal touch and proactive care goes towards maintaining long standing relationships.

content.content: Marc Peter- President

Marc is the co-founder and president. With more than 30 years of industry experience, Marc managed Seminole Energy’s marketing business in the Rockies and upper Midwest before starting WoodRiver Energy in 2014.
Starr McNamara- CFO

Starr McNamara comes to WoodRiver Energy with more than 20 years of experience in a variety of senior management roles in disciplines that include finance, accounting, legal, audit, tax, human resources and operations. In her role as CFO to WoodRiver Energy, Starr provides financial leadership to the company, oversees all accounting and administrative aspects, and works closely with the other executive roles to set company strategy.
Don Krattenmaker- Vice President

VP of Business Development, Don, has twenty years of experience in trading and selling natural gas. Most recently he headed up a sales office of 25 people marketing gas in the Rocky Mountain and upper Midwest states. At WoodRiver, Don heads up the company’s business development efforts and supports the company’s on-going sales and marketing efforts.
Stacci Urbom- Vice President

VP of Sales, Stacci, has 20 years of experience of marketing natural gas in Nebraska and Iowa. In that time she has developed a wealth of knowledge and experience in the business and the region. With WoodRiver, Stacci is leading the effort to develop WoodRiver’s market position in the region.
Michael Ray- Director of Risk and Supply
With 8 years of risk management experience, Michael Ray works to lock in natural gas rate to provide our customers with rate certainty.
